<item>
            <title>[SPR-2794] DispatcherPortlet does not restore LocaleContextHolder and RequestContextHolder state</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2794</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Finally blocks in DispatcherPortlet.doActionService() and doRenderService() reset Thread-bound references held by by LocaleContextHolder and RequestContextHolder. This is problematic for clients that require access to scoped beans following DispatcherPortlet invocation. For example, a portlet container may depend on request- or session-scoped beans initialized by a ServletRequestListener or Filter. Such a container likely expects those beans to be accessible for the complete lifetime of a request and may be unpleasantly suprised by DispatcherPortlet&apos;s aggressive cleanup behavior. Ideally, DispatcherPortlet would behave like DispatcherServlet and restore the received state of LocaleContextHolder and RequestContextHolder after it completes its internal request handling.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
            <key id="15400">SPR-2794</key>
            <summary>DispatcherPortlet does not restore LocaleContextHolder and RequestContextHolder state</summary>
